nment''</center>\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>3</center> || colspan=\"13\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"3\" | <center>''The Big Top''</center> || colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>4</center> || colspan=\"14\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#3F6;\" | <center>''Platform 15''</center>\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>3</center> || colspan=\"15\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#3F6;\" | <center>''The Walking Dead: Living Nightmare''</center>\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>1</center> || colspan=\"15\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"1\" | <center>''The Walking Dead: Sanctum''</center> || colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>2</center> || colspan=\"16\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#3F6;\" | <center>''The Walking Dead: Do or Die''</center>\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>1</center> || colspan=\"16\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"1\" | <center>''Vulcan Peak''</center> || colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>2</center> || colspan=\"16\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#3F6;\" | <center>''Terror at Amity High''</center> || colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>1</center> || colspan=\"16\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"1\" | <center>''The Big Top: Showtime''</center> || colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>1</center> || colspan=\"16\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"1\" | <center>''Dead Creek Woods''</center> || colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>1</center> || colspan=\"17\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#3F6;\" | <center>''Creek Freak Massacre''</center>\n|-\n| colspan=\"1\"| <center>2</center> || colspan=\"16\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\" |  || colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#3F6;\" | <center>''Screamplexx Cinema''</center>\n|}\n\n{{Color box|#FFFFFF|border=darkgray}}&nbsp;\u2013 Previous Fright Night attraction.\n{{Color box|#3F6|border=darkgray}}&nbsp;\u2013 Current Fright Night attraction.\n\n==Hotel==\n\nGuests can stay over on-park at the 'Thorpe Shark Hotel', comprising 90-rooms converted from [[shipping container]]s with a link to facilities in the adjacent Dome. The accommodation takes its name from its shark head entrance feature built from scrapped park signage.\n\nThe hotel initially opened in 2013 as 'The Crash Pad', run by external company [[Snoozebox]]. The temporary development was purchased by the park the following year and rebranded as the Thorpe Shark Hotel.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sim|first1=Nick|title=Thorpe Park names new hotel for 2014 as Thorpe Shark Hotel|url=http://www.themeparktourist.com/news/20140313/16793/thorpe-park-names-new-hotel-2014-thorpe-shark-hotel|website=Theme Park Tourist|accessdate=18 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nThorpe Park had originally been planning to build a permanent 250-bed hotel as far back as 2006. This would have been located on the opposite side of the lake, on the site of former excavation works, featuring a lakeside bar, health club and restaurant.\n\nThe development was pitched again following the installation of 'The Crash Pad' to \"test market conditions\". The park received planning permission to construct the permanent hotel in 2014, with construction planned to begin in 2016 and an opening in 2018. However, the hotel was never constructed and the Shark Hotel's planning permission was extended by 10 years instead.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Total Thorpe Park|first1=|title=Thorpe Park Hotel planning|url=http://www.totalthorpepark.co.uk/features/futurehotel.shtml|website=Theme Park Tourist|accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Developments ==\n\nIn 2010, the park outlined a 5-year development plan that outlined new coasters for 2012 (The Swarm) and 2015, as well as a permanent lakeside hotel. No application was ever submitted for the 2015 development and the intended site of coaster behind The Swarm remains vacant.\n\n==Incidents==\n{{Main|Incidents at European amusement parks#Thorpe Park|l1=Incidents at European amusement parks: Thorpe Park}}\n\n==Gallery==\n\n:''Main gallery: [[commons:Thorpe Park Resort|Thorpe Park Resort at WikiCommons]]''\n<!-- If possible, use only pictures unique to this park. No fourteen-in-the-dozen pictures that could be made in every park/zoo -->\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Surrey}}\n* [[Merlin Entertainments]]\n* [[The Tussauds Group]]\n* [[RMC Group]]\n* \"[[Thorpe Park (The Inbetweeners)|Thorpe Park]]\", an episode of ''[[The Inbetweeners]]'' where the main characters visit Thorpe Park\n* ''[[Primeval (TV series)|Primeval]]'' - the third episode of Series 2 featured the park under a fictitious name.\n* [[Staines railway station]]\n* [[Alton Towers]]\n* [[Chessington World of Adventures]]\n* [[Theme Park]]\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikimedia|collapsible=true|c=Category:Thorpe Park|voy=Thorpe park|species=no|v=no|wikt=no|d=Q2301819}}\n\n* {{Official website|http://www.thorpepark.com/}}\n* [http://www.merlinentertainments.biz/ Merlin Entertainments]\n* [http://thorpeparkmania.co.uk/ Official Fan Website]\n\n{{Portal bar|United Kingdom}}\n{{TP Coasters}}\n{{Merlin attractions}}\n{{John Wardley}}\n{{British theme parks}}\n{{Runnymede}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Thorpe Park| ]]\n[[Category:1979 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Amusement parks in England]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Surrey]]\n[[Category:Merlin Entertainments Group]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Surrey]]\n[[Category:Amusement parks opened in 1979]]\n[[Category:Parks and attractions with Angry Birds exhibits]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7d:bb9e:da00:c56f:809a:419d:2941